result.execSummary:
The defendant Santos Cuaquehua Itzacahua was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sexual Assault of a Child Under 16 Years of Age, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to the sentences in Tremp. Co. Case Nos. 10 CF 100 and 11 CF 17.  Dodge Correctional as reception center.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant to pay all court costs, including the DNA surcharge.
Defendant not to consume alcohol.  No drugs without a prescription.  Defendant not to enter taverns.  Defendant to have no contact with the victim, their residence, or their family.

Defendant to participate and complete programming as deemed appropriate by COMPAS assessment and Probation Agent.  Defendant to submit a DNA sample.  Defendant to obtain a Psychosexual Evaluation and participate in Sex Offender Treatment.  Defendant to register with the Sex Offender Registry.  Defendant to submit letter of apology to the victim, through the Agent.
